On the surface this is a nice intimate environment. I must admit the oxtails were really good however the catfish was too heavily seasoned in that it completely overpowered the fish itself. Another note is the Friday bar staff beware! During my last visit at 2:45pm I came in with a friend, we both ordered take out and made it absolutely clear that we were making separate orders with separate checks. I paid with my card and my friend paid in cash. The next day I noticed that my card had been charged separately for both orders. I returned to this establishment and spoke with the manager his response was that my friend did not pay his check so the bar server decided to charge my card for his order. I saw my friend pay his bill in cash and he left a $12.00 tip. So I have major problems here, first my card was ran after I left. How is this even possible if card information does not store in restaurants once a transaction is complete. This says to me that the bar server obviously copied my card information. It is also obvious that the bar server kept the cash from my friend with the assumption that I would not notice the charge. Be careful because the bar server on Friday will steal you credit card information. And the manager is an empty suit who did nothing but accuse me of having a dishonest friend. However if he would have reviewed the camera footage he would see my friend pay cash for his check. The staff is dishonest an unaccomadating. So check you balance if you use your card at Ja Grill you might realize that you have been charged multiple times. Ja Grill seems to add charges to your card even when you are not there!

We had a reservation for 7:30. We arrived early and thought we would have drinks in the bar until our table was ready. The hostess Miss Kent was amazing. She said Herb Kent was her father. Extremely friendly she got us a table within five minutes. It was very busy the entire place was packed. We were very impressed with speed in which we were seated. We were a party of five. The server came over quickly and took our drink orders. From this point things went down hill quickly. It took forever to get our appetizers. And there was more than thirty minutes between the time we were done with the 1st course and the arrival of the 2nd course. I had the lamb chops medium rare they were the best I've eve had. Someone else ordered them medium and they came out well done and warm not pipping hot. The  entrees came out over a 15 minute period not all together as the should. The jerk chicken was dry. Not enjoyable at all. The server seemed to be in the weeds all night. To sum things up the rum punch was good. My  lamb chops were great unlike my girlfriends. This place is loud and busy and that was fine, in fact I liked that. The service left much to be desired. The kitchen needs more consistency with the foods that they put out everything should be hot and taste the same. Maybe it was a bad night. Perhaps we'll give them another shot.
